cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is about exemplar-based face sketch synthesis, which is a computer vision problem related to image processing and analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a new method to improve the efficiency of the neighbor selection process, which involves selecting similar images from a training dataset. This method involves random sampling, which is a technique used in machine learning and optimization algorithms, so it is also likely to be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the method, which is related to performance optimization, so it could be classified under cs.MM (Multimedia) as well. Finally, the paper mentions the potential application of the proposed method to other face image transformation problems, which could be related to computer graphics and visualization, so it could also be classified under cs.GR (Graphics).
